Bootstrap
    - what is it?
        - it is a CSS framework
        - allows us to quickly create a responsive website with minimal CSS
    - consists of 2 main things
        - Components
            - buttons, navbars
        - Grid system
            - layout
    - including Bootstrap
        - <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-+0n0xVW2eSR5OomGNYDnhzAbDsOXxcvSN1TPprVMTNDbiYZCxYbOOl7+AMvyTG2x" crossorigin="anonymous">
    - including bootstrap js parts
        - <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-gtEjrD/SeCtmISkJkNUaaKMoLD0//ElJ19smozuHV6z3Iehds+3Ulb9Bn9Plx0x4" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    
    - components to know
        - container : contains content, adds responsiveness and padding and a font change
            - container-fluid : same as standard container, but fills 100% width
            - container-sm, md, lg, xl
        - btn : a bootstrap styled button 
            - btn btn-primary : a blue button 
            - btn btn-outline-primary : a blue outlined button 
            - btn btn-sm : samll button 
        - lead : emphasizes text 
        - mb-0 : margin bottom zero
        - blockquote
            - blockquote-footer
        - text-center : center text  
        - text-primary : primary colored text 
        - bg-warning : yellow background element
        - badge : creates a badge within an element 
            - badge bage-secondary : grey badge 
            - badge-pill 
        - btn-group
            - class="btn-group" role="group"
        - alert
            - alert alert-primary 
            - alert-heading
        - close
        - fade
        - show 

    - colors to know
        - primary: blue 
        - secondary: grey 
        - success: green 
        - danger: red 
        - warning: yellow
        - info: teal 
        - light: white 
        - dark: black
        - link: a link      

    - grid system
        - helps to layout content
        - must be using a container anytime you want to use bootstrap grid
        - sizes (size units)
            - small: sm
                - 540px
            - medium: md 
                - 720px
            - large: lg 
                - 960px
            - extra large: xl 
                - 1140px

        - every row in bootstrap grid has 12 units to "give away"
            - so if you have 3 columns, they each take up 4 units 
        - classes
            - col-2 : 2 units column
            - no-gutters
            - col-sm-4 : once the small break point is hit use 4 units
            - justify-content : flex analog 
            - align-self : flex analog 

    - forms
        - class
            - form-control : base form contianer
            - form-group : groups labels and inputs (doesn't do much)
            - form-row

    - navbars
        - refer to docs  
    
    - icons
        - free icons available to use in your components 
        - they are svg's 